⭐ 1. Gin

Most popular Go web framework

Very fast and lightweight

Used for REST APIs and microservices

Easy to learn

⭐ Example use: Backend APIs, dashboards

⭐ 2. Echo

High-performance web framework

Simple routing and middleware

Good for building REST APIs

Clean syntax

⭐ 3. Fiber

Inspired by Express.js (Node.js)

Very fast

Easy for beginners

Great for APIs

⭐ 4. Beego

Full-stack Go framework

MVC architecture

Built-in ORM

Good for large applications

⭐ 5. Buffalo

Rails-like experience in Go

Full-stack framework

Includes routing, templates, assets

Opinionated structure

⭐ 6. Revel

High-productivity framework

MVC style

Hot reload support

Good for traditional web apps

⭐ 7. Chi

Lightweight router (not full framework)

Very flexible

Used for microservices

Minimalistic

⭐ 8. Standard Go (net/http)

Built-in Go HTTP package

No external framework needed

Very powerful

Used in production widely

⭐ 9. When to choose Go frameworks

High-performance backend

Microservices

APIs

Cloud & DevOps systems

⭐ 10. One-line summary

Go frameworks are mainly used for fast, scalable backend services and APIs.

⭐ Quick recommendation

Beginner → Gin / Fiber

Microservices → Chi / Gin

Full-stack → Buffalo / Beego
